<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h1>What is a thought record?<h1>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <p>To assist patients in their quest, cognitive-behavioral therapists uses a tool called "thought record". This has typically been a sheet of paper with 7 columns, in which the patient has to fill out when they are not in their therapy sessions.</p>

    <p>In a patient's day-to-day life, when he/she encounters an emotional trigger, they are asked to record it on this sheet of paper. As patients get used to filling in their thought record sheet, they begin to learn how to step back in situations and find a more realistic perspective on their own.</p>

    <p>There are many variations on the thought record but it usually consists of these items:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Situation: What's the emotional trigger? What happened?</li>
        <li>Moods: How did it make you feel physically and emotionally?</li>
        <li>Automatic thoughts/images: What kind of thoughts immediately came to mind?</li>
        <li>Supporting facts: What evidence can you find that supports your belief?</li>
        <li>Disproving facts: What evidence disproves your belief?</li>
        <li>Alternative perspective: Is there another way to view this situation?</li>
        <li>Rate mood again: How do you feel now?</li>
      </ul>
  </div>
</div>
